## Accessing cohort info inside your Worker

After routing happens, you can read how the request was routed via `ctx.version`:

```ts
export default {
  async fetch(request, env, ctx) {
    const { cohort, override, key, metadata } = ctx.version;

    // cohort:   which cohort header was matched ("canary", "ent", etc.)
    // override: version ID if an override header was used
    // key:      version key if a version-key header was used
    // metadata: { id, tag, timestamp } of the running version

    console.log(`cohort: ${cohort}, version: ${metadata.id}`);
  }
};
```

Use this for logging and observability. If you see `cohort: undefined` for a user
who should have a cohort, something broke in your setup.

