## Setup checklist — from zero to working

```
Step 1: Deploy v1 of your Worker
        wrangler deploy

Step 2: Make changes, deploy v2
        wrangler deploy

Step 3: Call Cloudflare API to create the cohort deployment
        (maps cohort names → version IDs, sets percentages)

Step 4: Pick your approach and set it up:

        Gateway Entrypoint?
        □ Write cohort resolution logic in your Worker
        □ Add enable_ctx_exports to wrangler.toml
        □ Add export class Service extends WorkerEntrypoint
        □ Deploy

        Transform Rule?
        □ Set cohort cookie in your login endpoint (backend)
        □ Create Transform Rule in Cloudflare dashboard
        □ Test that cookie → header flow works

        Upstream Worker?
        □ Build auth Worker with cohort stamping logic
        □ Add Service Binding in wrangler.toml
        □ Point your domain at the auth Worker
        □ Deploy both Workers

Step 5: Add logging
        console.log(ctx.version.cohort)

Step 6: Verify in logs that users are hitting the right cohorts
```

